---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy"
  description="How Tutelare handles personal information submitted through the site and visitor analytics."
>
  <h1
    class="font-semibold leading-tight mb-6"
    style="font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem)"
  >
    Privacy
  </h1>

  <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-ink-muted)">
    Last updated: <time datetime="2026-05-24">May 24, 2026</time>
  </p>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3" style="font-family: var(--font-serif)">
      What we collect
    </h2>
    <p>
      We collect two kinds of information:
    </p>
    <ol class="pl-5 flex flex-col gap-2">
      <li>
        <strong>What you send us.</strong> When you email
        <a href="mailto:sthurlow@tutelare.ai">sthurlow@tutelare.ai</a> or use a
        contact form on the site, we receive the contents of that message and your
        email address.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Visitor analytics via Google Analytics 4.</strong> We use Google
        Analytics to count visits to the site and understand which pages are read.
        Google Analytics sets cookies in your browser and collects standard web
        analytics data: pages viewed, referrer URL, approximate location derived
        from your IP address (country and region only — we do not store full IP
        addresses), browser and device information, and timestamps. We do not
        enable Google Signals, demographic inference, or cross-device tracking.
        Data is retained for two months.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3" style="font-family: var(--font-serif)">
      How we use it
    </h2>
    <p>
      We use the information you send us solely to respond to your message and to
      follow up on potential engagements. We use analytics data in aggregate to
      understand which writing and which pages prospects find useful. We do not
      sell or share your personal information with third parties.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3" style="font-family: var(--font-serif)">
      Opting out of analytics
    </h2>
    <p>
      You can prevent Google Analytics from collecting data about your visit by:
    </p>
    <ul class="pl-5 flex flex-col gap-2">
      <li>Enabling your browser's Do Not Track or Global Privacy Control setting.</li>
      <li>Installing an ad blocker that blocks analytics scripts (uBlock Origin, Privacy Badger, etc.).</li>
      <li>
        Installing
        <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" rel="noopener">
          Google's official Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on
        </a>.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3" style="font-family: var(--font-serif)">
      How long we retain it
    </h2>
    <p>
      Analytics data is retained for two months and then automatically deleted by
      Google. Correspondence is retained for the duration of any active engagement
      plus a reasonable business-record retention period. You can request deletion
      of your correspondence at any time by emailing
      <a href="mailto:sthurlow@tutelare.ai">sthurlow@tutelare.ai</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3" style="font-family: var(--font-serif)">
      Your rights
    </h2>
    <p>
      If you are located in the European Union, the United Kingdom, California, or
      any other jurisdiction with applicable data protection law, you may have
      additional rights including access, correction, and deletion of your personal
      information. Contact
      <a href="mailto:sthurlow@tutelare.ai">sthurlow@tutelare.ai</a> to exercise
      these rights.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
